      "author_association": "MEMBER",
      "body": "The fact that `MemPoolAccept::AcceptSingleTransaction` exists and that the RPC accepts an array seems to suggest this is planned but I don't know much about who's working on/thinking about what. Is there ongoing work that would enable this as a side effect?\r\n\r\nI think this would be very nice to have. Doing this for non-chained transactions would probably have little value (just make separate calls), but I definitely see why we'd want to test accept chained transactions.\r\n\r\nI'm not 100% sure what needs to be done to implement this. My intuition is that this requires making a temporary copy of chainstate/mempool on which we apply each transaction so that we can use it for the ones that come after it. Also, won't ordering matter? If a child comes before a parent in the array, should we make a temporary orphan pool too? Seems nontrivial ðŸ¤” ",
